// INT during a block-op (LDIR). LDIR is interruptible — the silicon-faithful
// behaviour is that an INT during an LDIR iteration takes effect at the END
// of the current iteration, PC is rewound to the LDIR opcode address (so
// the block op resumes after the ISR), and only THEN does the INTA M-cycle
// fire. After RST 38h, the IM1 ISR runs to HALT.
@0000
ED 56              // IM 1
FB                 // EI
21 00 02           // LD HL,0x0200      (source)
11 00 03           // LD DE,0x0300      (destination)
01 10 00           // LD BC,0x0010      (16 bytes)
ED B0              // LDIR              (interruptible block move)
76                 // HALT
@0038
76                 // HALT (IM1 vector)
@0200
00 11 22 33 44 55 66 77 88 99 AA BB CC DD EE FF
